{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"read-grape-coin","assignee":"claude","description":"## Why\n\n`server.json` is the MCP registry front-door contract, but it has drifted from\nthe real config surface. It lists only `REBAR_ROOT`, `REBAR_MCP_READONLY`, and\nthe **deprecated** `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_RECONCILE_LIVE`, while the actual gates are\n`mcp.allow_llm` (`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM`) and `mcp.allow_jira_sync`\n(`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC`). Users see the LLM/reconcile tools appear but fail\nat call time with no manifest hint, and new installs inherit deprecated\nterminology. Nothing prevents this from re-drifting.\n\n## What\n\n- Update `server.json` `environmentVariables` to the current contract: add\n  `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` and `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC` with accurate\n  descriptions; keep `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_RECONCILE_LIVE` only if explicitly labeled\n  a deprecated alias (prefer replacing it with the current name).\n- Add a **CI drift-guard** that compares the manifest's advertised env-var set\n  against the canonical gate list in code (the `REBAR_MCP_*` env gates read in\n  `mcp_server.py` / the readonly+allow gates), failing the build on divergence —\n  mirroring the existing prompt-index / criteria-routing drift gates in\n  `.github/workflows/test.yml`.\n\n## Scope\n\n`server.json` + one CI gate (a small script under `scripts/` or a step in\n`.github/workflows/test.yml`). Identify the single source of truth for the env\ngates so the guard has an authoritative list to diff against. No behavior change\nto the server itself.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `server.json` advertises `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` and\n  `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC` with correct descriptions.\n- [ ] The deprecated `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_RECONCILE_LIVE` is removed or explicitly\n  marked as a deprecated alias.\n- [ ] A CI gate fails when `server.json`'s env-var set diverges from the\n  canonical `REBAR_MCP_*` gate list in code.\n- [ ] The gate passes on the corrected manifest; `make lint` stays green.","id":"b49a-6864-e035-4f65","parent_id":"b02d-10bc-07ee-49e7","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Fix server.json MCP env/config contract and add a CI drift-guard"},"env_id":"58e9f32e-f999-436d-9c1a-5d0eef5c9903","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783148923677290954,"uuid":"bd412457-d67a-4711-b4d0-4ff7146003b8"}